<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Multi-tenant from the ground up</h2>
	<p>Every tenant in a partner account has its own portal scope, its own caller IDs, its own emergency-service records, its own users, and its own CDRs. One office or a hundred offices, the workflow is the same: add the tenant, assign numbers, register devices, place a call.</p>
	<p>Hosted PBX is billed per tenant and per extension — line-item rates published on the <a href="/pricing/#pbx">pricing page</a>. Designed for organizations and for the integrators who resell to them.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block faq-block">
	<h2>PBX FAQ</h2>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Can we keep existing desk phones?</summary>
		<p>Device compatibility depends on SIP support, firmware, provisioning, and security policy. Bring your own device is allowed, but its management, configuration, and support are solely the customer's responsibility. We highly recommend using VoiceTel devices and software applications.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Can hosted PBX use VoiceTel numbers?</summary>
		<p>Yes, numbers and emergency-service records are managed through the VoiceTel number workflow. The PBX product requires at least one emergency number per physical address.</p>
	</details>
</section>

